ssibly\nCompton-thick, AGNs in some of these objects. Two of these faint sources were\nfound to have X-ray counterparts to their double optical and infrared nuclei.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 3 Aug 2005 18:14:24 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
